      <section eId="sec_46_9_3">
        <num>46-9-3</num>
        <content>
          <p>In order for a common carrier to avail himself of the act of God exception under Code Section 46-9-1 or the contractual exception under Code Section 46-9-2, he must establish not only that the act of God or the contractually excepted fact ultimately occasioned the loss but that his own negligence did not contribute thereto.</p>
          <p>(Civil Code 1895, ยง 2265; Civil Code 1910, ยง 2713; Code 1933, ยง 18-103.)</p>
